@page "/architecture"

<div class="space-y-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-gray-800">Project Architecture Overview</h1>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-xl border border-gray-100 space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-teal-700">C# .NET Blazor Web App Structure</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
            This application employs a classic **Three-Tier Architecture** pattern, ensuring separation of concerns, scalability, and maintainability.
            Blazor allows us to unify the presentation and business logic layers using C#.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Architecture Breakdown -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

        <!-- Presentation Layer -->
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-xl border-t-4 border-teal-500 space-y-3">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-teal-700">1. Presentation Layer (UI)</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
                **Technology:** Razor Components (`.razor`) and Tailwind CSS.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                Handles all client-side interaction, routing, and rendering. Components are organized in `Pages` and `Components/Layout`. The Blazor Server model manages UI state and DOM updates via a SignalR connection.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Business Logic Layer -->
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-xl border-t-4 border-indigo-500 space-y-3">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-indigo-700">2. Business Logic Layer</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
                **Technology:** C# Services and Models (e.g., `UserService.cs`, `WorkoutModel.cs`).
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                Contains the core application logic: goal calculation, data validation, and rules for fitness tracking. Services are registered in `Program.cs` and injected into Razor components.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Data Access Layer -->
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-xl border-t-4 border-yellow-500 space-y-3">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-yellow-700">3. Data Access Layer (DAL)</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
                **Technology:** Entity Framework Core (Mock/Planned) connecting to Azure SQL.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                Responsible for connecting to the database, performing CRUD operations, and managing data persistence. This layer keeps the Business Logic layer unaware of the underlying database technology.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>